WEBVTT

00:21.380 --> 00:24.180
CHAPTER XIX.

00:25.500 --> 00:31.060
The library looked tranquil enough as I entered it, and the Sibyl, if Sibyl she

00:31.060 --> 00:36.680
were, was seated snugly enough in an easy chair at the chimney corner. She had on a

00:36.680 --> 00:42.100
red cloak and a black bonnet, or rather a broad brim gypsy hat tied down with a

00:42.100 --> 00:46.860
striped handkerchief under her chin. An extinguished candle stood on the table.

00:47.380 --> 00:52.000
She was bending over the fire and seemed reading in a little black book, like a

00:52.000 --> 00:57.700
book by the light of the blaze. She muttered the words to herself as most old

00:57.700 --> 01:02.820
women do while she read. She did not desist immediately on my entrance. It

01:02.820 --> 01:07.080
appeared she wished to finish a paragraph. I stood on the rug and warmed

01:07.080 --> 01:10.960
my hands, which were rather cold with sitting at a distance from the drawing

01:10.960 --> 01:16.760
room fire. I felt now as composed as ever I did in my life. There was nothing

01:16.760 --> 01:21.800
indeed in the gypsy's appearance to trouble one's calm. She shut her book and

01:21.800 --> 01:27.420
slowly looked up. Her hat brim partially shaded her face, yet I could see as she

01:27.420 --> 01:33.560
raised it that it was a strange one. It looked all brown and black. Elf-locks

01:33.560 --> 01:37.600
bristled out from beneath a white band which passed under her chin and came

01:37.600 --> 01:43.340
half over her cheeks, or rather jaws. Her eyes confronted me at once with a bold

01:43.340 --> 01:44.380
and direct gaze.

01:45.000 --> 01:51.580
Well, and you want your fortune told? She said in a voice as decided as her glance,

01:51.820 --> 01:56.940
as harsh as her features. I don't care about it, mother. You may please

01:56.940 --> 02:03.200
yourself, but I ought to warn you. I have no faith. It's like your impotence to say

02:03.200 --> 02:08.940
so. I expect it of you. I heard it in your step as you crossed the threshold.

02:09.700 --> 02:16.860
Did you? You have a quick ear. I have, and a quick eye, and a quick brain. You need

02:16.860 --> 02:22.700
them all in your trade. I do, especially when I've customers like you to deal

02:22.700 --> 02:31.820
with. Why don't you tremble? I'm not cold. Why don't you turn pale? I am not sick.

02:31.820 --> 02:40.640
Why don't you consult my art? I'm not silly. The old crone knickered a laugh

02:40.640 --> 02:45.500
under her bonnet and bandage. She then drew out a short black pipe, and lighting

02:45.500 --> 02:50.760
it began to smoke. Having indulged a while in this sedative, she raised her

02:50.760 --> 02:55.460
bent body, took the pipe from her lips, and while gazing steadily at the fire,

02:55.460 --> 03:05.480
said very deliberately, You are cold, you are sick, and you are silly. Prove it, I

03:05.480 --> 03:14.260
rejoined. I will, in a few words. You are cold because you are alone. No contact

03:14.260 --> 03:19.650
strikes the fire from you that is in you. You are sick because the best of

03:19.650 --> 03:26.090
things, the highest and sweetest given to man, keeps far away from you. You are

03:26.090 --> 03:31.770
silly because you suffer as you may. You will not beckon it to approach, nor will

03:31.770 --> 03:38.270
you stir one step to meet it where it waits you. She again put her short black

03:38.270 --> 03:44.290
pipe to her lips, and renewed her smoking with vigor. You might say all that to

03:44.290 --> 03:49.630
almost anyone who you knew lived as a solitary dependent in a great house. I

03:49.630 --> 03:56.070
might say it to almost anyone, but would it be true of almost anyone? In my

03:56.070 --> 04:03.010
circumstances? Yes, just so, in your circumstances, but find me another

04:03.010 --> 04:09.990
precisely placed as you are. It would be easy to find you thousands. You could

04:09.990 --> 04:16.490
scarcely find me one. If you knew it, you are peculiarly situated. Very near

04:16.490 --> 04:24.410
happiness, yes, within reach of it. The materials are all prepared. There only

04:24.410 --> 04:31.390
wants a movement to combine them. Chance laid them somewhat apart. Let them be

04:31.390 --> 04:38.750
once approached, and bliss results. I don't understand enigmas. I never could

04:38.750 --> 04:45.310
guess a riddle in my life. If you wish me to speak more plainly, show me your palm.

04:46.290 --> 04:53.210
And I must cross it with silver, I suppose? To be sure. I gave her a shilling.

04:54.050 --> 04:58.570
She put it into an old stocking-foot, which she took out of her pocket, and

04:58.570 --> 05:04.410
having tied it round and returned it, she told me to hold out my hand. I did. She

05:04.410 --> 05:10.130
arched her face to the palm, and poured over it without touching it. It is too

05:10.690 --> 05:18.430
said she. I can make nothing of such a hand as that, almost without lines. Besides,

05:18.870 --> 05:27.990
what is in a palm? Destiny is not written there. I believe you, said I. No, she

05:27.990 --> 05:34.810
continued. It is in the face, on the forehead, about the eyes, in the lines of

05:34.810 --> 05:42.170
the mouth. Kneel and lift up your head. Ah, now you are coming to reality, I said

05:42.170 --> 05:47.630
as I obeyed her. I shall begin to put some faith in you presently. I knelt

05:47.630 --> 05:51.810
within half a yard of her. She stirred the fire so that a ripple of light broke

05:51.810 --> 05:56.790
from the disturbed coal. The glare, however, as she sat, only threw her face

05:56.790 --> 06:04.790
into deeper shadow. Mine, it illumined. I wonder with what feelings you came to me

06:04.790 --> 06:10.970
tonight, she said when she had examined me a while. I wonder what thoughts are

06:10.970 --> 06:15.630
busy in your heart during all the hours you sit in yonder room with the fine

06:15.630 --> 06:21.230
people flitting before you like shapes in a magic lantern, just as little

06:21.230 --> 06:26.010
sympathetic communion passing between you and them as if they were really mere

06:26.010 --> 06:34.710
shadows of human forms and not the actual substance. I feel tired

06:34.710 --> 06:42.690
often, sleepy sometimes, but seldom sad. Then you have some secret hope to boy

06:42.690 --> 06:49.470
you up and please you with whispers of the future? Not I. The utmost I hope is

06:49.470 --> 06:54.050
to save enough money out of my earnings to set up a school some day in a little

06:54.050 --> 07:00.710
house rented by myself. A mean nutriment for the spirit to exist on, and sitting

07:00.710 --> 07:07.370
in that window seat. You see, I know your habits. You have learned them from the

07:07.370 --> 07:15.090
servants. Ah, you think yourself sharp. Well, perhaps I have. To speak truth, I

07:15.090 --> 07:20.810
have an acquaintance with one of them, Mrs. Poole. I started to my feet when I

07:20.810 --> 07:25.990
heard the name. You have, have you? thought I. There is diablerie in the

07:28.390 --> 07:35.430
Don't be alarmed, continued the strange being. She is a safe hand, is Mrs. Poole.

07:35.730 --> 07:41.590
Close and quiet. Anyone may repose confidence in her. But as I was saying,

07:41.990 --> 07:46.930
sitting in that window seat, do you think of nothing but your future school? Have

07:46.930 --> 07:51.150
you no present interest in any of the company who occupy the sofas and chairs

07:51.150 --> 07:57.650
before you? Is there not one face you study, one figure whose movements you

07:57.650 --> 08:04.010
follow with at least curiosity? I like to observe all the faces and all the

08:04.010 --> 08:11.790
figures. But you never single one from the rest? Or it may be two? I do

08:11.790 --> 08:16.970
frequently, when the gestures or looks of a pair seem telling a tale. It amuses me

08:16.970 --> 08:25.950
watch them. What tale do you like best to hear? Oh, I have not much choice. They

08:25.950 --> 08:30.430
generally run on the same theme, courtship, and promise to end in the same

08:30.430 --> 08:38.570
catastrophe, marriage. And do you like that monotonous theme? Positively I don't

08:38.570 --> 08:45.210
care about it. It is nothing to me. Nothing to you? When lady, young and full

08:45.210 --> 08:51.210
of life and health, charming with beauty and endowed with the gifts of rank and

08:51.210 --> 09:01.810
fortune, sits and smiles in the eyes of a gentleman you... I what? You know. And

09:01.810 --> 09:07.770
perhaps think well of. I don't know the gentleman here. I have scarcely

09:07.770 --> 09:12.550
interchanged a syllable with one of them. And as to thinking well of them, I

09:12.550 --> 09:18.810
respectable and stately and middle-aged, and others young, dashing, handsome and

09:18.810 --> 09:23.090
lively. But certainly they are all at liberty to be the recipients of whose

09:23.090 --> 09:28.270
smiles they please, without my feeling disposed to consider the transaction of

09:28.270 --> 09:34.810
any moment to me. You don't know the gentleman here. You have not exchanged a

09:34.810 --> 09:41.230
syllable with one of them. Will you say that of the master of the house? He is

09:41.230 --> 09:48.190
not at home. A profound remark. A most ingenious quibble. He went to Millcote

09:48.190 --> 09:52.870
this morning, and will be back here tonight or tomorrow. Does that

09:52.870 --> 09:58.110
circumstance exclude him from the list of your acquaintance? Blot him, as it were,

09:58.210 --> 10:04.490
out of existence? No, but I can scarcely see what Mr. Rochester has to do with

10:04.490 --> 10:09.710
the theme you had introduced. I was talking of ladies smiling in the eyes of

10:09.710 --> 10:14.730
the gentleman, and of late so many smiles have been shed into Mr. Rochester's

10:14.730 --> 10:20.190
eyes that they overflow like two cups filled above the brim. Have you never

10:20.190 --> 10:26.310
remarked that? Mr. Rochester has a right to enjoy the society of his guests.

10:27.770 --> 10:33.030
No question about his right, but have you never observed that, of all the tales

10:33.030 --> 10:38.550
told here about matrimony, Mr. Rochester has been favoured with the most lively

10:38.550 --> 10:43.670
and the most continuous? The eagerness of a listener quickens the tongue of a

10:43.670 --> 10:48.590
narrator. I said this rather to myself than to the gypsy, whose strange talk,

10:48.750 --> 10:54.170
voice, manner, had by this time wrapped me in a kind of dream. One unexpected

10:54.170 --> 10:58.410
sentence came from her lips after another, till I got involved in a web of

10:58.410 --> 11:03.370
mystification, and wondered what unseen spirit had been sitting for weeks by my

11:04.050 --> 11:10.570
watching its workings, and taking record of every pulse. Eagerness of a listener,

11:11.470 --> 11:19.110
repeated she. Yes, Mr. Rochester has sat by the hour, his ear inclined to the

11:19.110 --> 11:24.650
fascinating lips that took such delight in their task of communicating, and Mr.

11:24.790 --> 11:29.950
Rochester was so willing to receive and looked so grateful for the pastime

11:29.950 --> 11:36.890
given him. You have noticed this? Grateful? I cannot remember detecting gratitude in

11:36.890 --> 11:44.170
his face. Detecting? You have analyzed then, and what did you detect if not gratitude?

11:45.190 --> 11:52.030
I said nothing. You have seen love, have you not, and looking forward you have

11:52.930 --> 12:01.290
and beheld his bride happy? Not exactly. Your witch's skill is rather at fault

12:01.290 --> 12:09.450
sometimes. What the devil have you seen then? Never mind. I came here to inquire,

12:09.510 --> 12:15.850
not to confess. Is it known that Mr. Rochester is to be married? Yes, and to

12:15.850 --> 12:22.710
beautiful Miss Ingram. Shortly? Appearances would warrant that conclusion,

12:23.250 --> 12:28.710
and no doubt, though with an audacity that once chastising out of you, you seem

12:28.710 --> 12:34.270
to question it, they will be a superlatively happy pair. He must love such

12:34.270 --> 12:40.790
a handsome, noble, witty, accomplished lady, and probably she loves him, or if

12:40.790 --> 12:46.530
not his purse, at least his purse. I know she considers the Rochester estate

12:46.530 --> 12:53.350
eligible to the last degree, though, God pardon me, I told her something on that

12:53.350 --> 12:58.430
point about an hour ago which made her look wondrous grave. The corners of her

12:58.430 --> 13:05.230
mouth fell half an inch. I would advise her black avest suitor to look out. If

13:05.230 --> 13:12.990
another comes with a longer or clearer rent roll, he's dished. But mother, I did

13:12.990 --> 13:18.550
not come to hear Mr. Rochester's fortune. I came to hear my own, and you have told

13:18.550 --> 13:26.750
me nothing of it. Your fortune is yet doubtful. When I examined your face, one

13:26.750 --> 13:33.150
trait contradicted another. Chance has meted you a measure of happiness, that I

13:33.150 --> 13:40.010
knew it before I came here this evening. She has laid it carefully on one side

13:40.010 --> 13:46.010
for you. I saw her do it. It depends on yourself to stretch out your hand and

13:46.010 --> 13:52.310
take it up, but whether you will do so is the problem I study. Kneel again on the

13:52.310 --> 13:59.950
rug. Don't keep me long. The fire scorches me. I knelt. She did not stoop

13:59.950 --> 14:06.450
towards me, but only gazed leaning back in her chair. She began muttering. The

14:06.450 --> 14:13.050
flame flickers in the eye. The eye shines like dew. It looks soft and full of

14:13.050 --> 14:20.130
feeling. It smiles at my jargon. It is susceptible. Impression follows

14:20.130 --> 14:27.410
impression through its clear sphere. Where it ceases to smile, it is sad. An

14:27.410 --> 14:34.090
unconscious lassitude weighs on the lid. That signifies melancholy resulting from

14:34.090 --> 14:41.430
loneliness. It turns from me. It will not suffer further scrutiny. It seems to deny

14:41.430 --> 14:46.850
by a mocking glance the truth of the discoveries I have already made. To

14:46.850 --> 14:52.410
disown the charge of both sensibility and chagrin, its pride and reserve only

14:52.410 --> 15:02.010
opinion. The eye is favorable. As to the mouth, it delights at times in laughter.

15:02.610 --> 15:08.450
It is disposed to impart all that the brain conceives. Though I dare say it would

15:08.450 --> 15:14.950
be silent on much the heart experiences. Mobile and flexible, it was never

15:14.950 --> 15:20.510
intended to be compressed in the eternal silence of solitude. It is a mouth which

15:20.510 --> 15:26.530
should speak much and smile often and have human affection for its interlocutor.

15:27.950 --> 15:35.150
That feature is too propitious. I see no enemy to a fortunate issue but in the

15:35.150 --> 15:41.390
brow. And that brow professes to say I can live alone if self-respect and

15:41.390 --> 15:48.810
circumstance require me so to do. I need not sell my soul to buy bliss. I have an

15:48.810 --> 15:54.050
inward treasure born with me which can keep me alive if all extraneous delights

15:54.050 --> 15:59.790
should be withheld or offered only at a price I cannot afford to give. The

15:59.790 --> 16:05.970
forehead declares reason sits firm and holds the reins and she will not let the

16:05.970 --> 16:11.830
feelings burst away and hurry her into wild chasms. The passions may rage

16:11.830 --> 16:18.550
furiously like true heathens as they are and the desires may imagine all sorts of

16:19.450 --> 16:26.190
but judgment shall still have the last word in every argument and the casting

16:26.190 --> 16:33.220
vote in every decision. Strong wind, earthquake, shock and fire may pass by

16:33.430 --> 16:39.940
but I shall follow the guiding of that still small voice which interprets the

16:39.940 --> 16:41.460
of conscience.

16:44.980 --> 16:53.780
Well said, forehead. Your declaration shall be respected. I have formed my plans,

16:54.640 --> 17:00.060
right plans I deem them, and in them I have attended to the claims of conscience,

17:00.520 --> 17:06.080
the counsels of reason. I know how soon youth would fade in the bloom parish,

17:06.080 --> 17:13.060
if in the cup of bliss offered but one drag of shame or one flavor of remorse

17:13.060 --> 17:20.020
were detected and I do not want sacrifice, sorrow, disillusion, such as not

17:20.020 --> 17:27.060
my taste. I wish to foster not to blight, to earn gratitude not to ring tears of

17:27.060 --> 17:34.620
blood, no nor of brine. My harvest must be in smiles, in endearments, in sweet.

17:34.620 --> 17:41.640
That will do. I think I rave in a kind of exquisite delirium. I should wish now to

17:41.640 --> 17:48.420
protract this moment ad infinitum but I dare not. So far I have governed myself

17:48.420 --> 17:54.120
thoroughly. I have acted as I inwardly swore I would act but further might try

17:54.120 --> 17:58.740
me beyond my strength. Rise, Miss Eyre, leave me, the play is played out.

18:01.140 --> 18:08.980
Where was I? Did I wake or sleep? Had I been dreaming? Did I dream still? The old

18:08.980 --> 18:15.000
woman's voice had changed, her accent, her gesture, and all were familiar to me

18:15.000 --> 18:20.900
as my own face in a glass, as the speech of my own tongue. I got up but did not

18:20.900 --> 18:28.400
go. I looked, I stirred the fire, and I looked again. But she drew her bonnet and

18:28.400 --> 18:34.820
bandage closer about her face, and again beckoned me to depart. The flame

18:34.820 --> 18:39.060
illuminated, her hand stretched out. Roused now and on the alert for

18:39.060 --> 18:44.560
discoveries, I at once noticed that hand. It was no more the withered limb of an

18:44.560 --> 18:49.700
eld than my own. It was a rounded supple member with smooth fingers

18:49.700 --> 18:55.040
symmetrically turned, a broad ring flashed on the little finger, and stooping

18:55.040 --> 19:01.060
forward, I looked at it and saw a gem I had seen a hundred times before. Again I

19:01.060 --> 19:06.640
looked at the face, which was no longer turned from me. On the contrary, the

19:06.640 --> 19:13.040
bonnet was doffed, the bandage displaced, the head advanced. Well, Jane, do you know

19:13.040 --> 19:25.020
me? asked the familiar voice. Only take off the red cloak, sir, and then, but the

19:25.020 --> 19:34.100
There then, off ye lendings. And Mr. Rochester stepped out of his disguise. Now, sir, what a strange idea.

19:34.760 --> 19:40.760
But well carried out, eh? Don't you think so? With the ladies you must have managed well.

19:41.140 --> 19:55.000
But not with you? You did not act the character of a gypsy with me. What

19:55.000 --> 20:01.300
you have been trying to draw me out. Or in. You have been talking nonsense to make me

20:01.300 --> 20:04.460
talk nonsense. It is scarcely fair, sir.

20:05.280 --> 20:06.940
Do you forgive me, Jane?

20:07.820 --> 20:13.980
I cannot tell till I have thought it all over. If, on reflection, I find I have fallen into

20:13.980 --> 20:18.880
no great absurdity, I shall try to forgive you. But it was not right.

20:19.960 --> 20:26.060
Oh, you have been very correct, very careful, very sensible.

20:26.960 --> 20:33.200
I reflected, and thought on the whole I had. It was a comfort, but indeed, I had been on

20:33.200 --> 20:38.140
my guard almost from the beginning of the interview. Something of masquerade I suspected.

20:38.860 --> 20:43.600
I knew gypsies and fortune-tellers did not express themselves as this seeming old woman

20:43.600 --> 20:50.300
had expressed herself. Besides, I had noted her feigned voice, her anxiety to conceal

20:50.300 --> 20:57.080
her features. But my mind had been running on Grace Poole, that living enigma, that mystery

20:57.080 --> 21:01.300
of mysteries as I considered her. I had never thought of Mr. Rochester.

21:02.520 --> 21:09.560
Well, he said, what are you musing about? What does that grave smile signify?

21:10.580 --> 21:16.300
Wonder and self-congratulations, sir. I have your permission to retire now, I suppose?

21:17.100 --> 21:21.800
No, stay a moment, and tell me what the people in the drawing-room yonder are doing.

21:23.040 --> 21:24.800
Discussing the gypsy, I dare say.

21:25.700 --> 21:28.600
Sit down. Let me hear what they said about me.

21:29.160 --> 21:34.560
I had better not stay long, sir. It must be near eleven o'clock. Oh, are you aware, Mr.

21:34.800 --> 21:38.300
Rochester, that a stranger has arrived here since you left this morning?

21:38.900 --> 21:44.440
A stranger? No. Who can it be? I expected no one. Is he gone?

21:45.400 --> 21:50.020
No. He said he had known you long, and that he could take the liberty of installing himself

21:50.020 --> 21:51.020
here till you returned.

21:51.620 --> 21:54.220
The devil he did! Did he give his name?

21:54.960 --> 22:00.780
His name is Mason, sir, and he comes from the West Indies. From Spanish town in Jamaica,

22:00.780 --> 22:07.380
I think. Mr. Rochester was standing near me. He had taken my hand, as if to lead me to

22:07.380 --> 22:14.620
a chair. As I spoke, he gave my wrist a convulsive grip. The smile on his lips froze. Apparently

22:14.620 --> 22:16.160
a spasm caught his breath.

22:17.860 --> 22:25.400
Mason, the West Indies, he said, in the tone one might fancy a speaking automaton to announce

22:25.400 --> 22:26.440
its single words.

22:26.940 --> 22:34.660
Mason, the West Indies, he reiterated, and he went over the syllables three times, growing

22:34.660 --> 22:39.700
in the interval of speaking whiter than ashes. He hardly seemed to know what he was doing.

22:40.260 --> 22:43.220
Do you feel ill, sir? I inquired.

22:44.000 --> 22:50.740
Jane, I've got a blow. I've got a blow, Jane, he staggered. Oh, lean on me, sir.

22:51.660 --> 22:55.080
Jane, you offered me your shoulder once before. Let me have it now.

22:56.000 --> 23:01.820
Yes, sir, yes, and my arm. He sat down and made me sit beside him.

23:02.520 --> 23:07.440
Holding my hand in both his own, he chafed it, gazing on me at the same time with the

23:07.440 --> 23:09.180
most troubled and dreary look.

23:10.220 --> 23:17.400
My little friend, said he, I wish I were in a quiet island with only you, and trouble

23:17.400 --> 23:20.980
and danger and hideous recollections removed from me.

23:21.640 --> 23:25.080
Can I help you, sir? I'd give my life to serve you.

23:26.360 --> 23:30.280
Jane, if aid is wanted, I'll seek it at your hands. I promise you that.

23:31.120 --> 23:35.900
Thank you, sir. Tell me what to do. I'll try at least to do it.

23:37.480 --> 23:42.020
Fetch me now, Jane, a glass of wine from the dining-room. They will be at supper there,

23:42.180 --> 23:44.640
and tell me if Mason is with them and what he is doing.

23:45.680 --> 23:51.320
I went. I found all the party in the dining-room at supper, as Mr. Rochester had said. They

23:51.320 --> 23:56.620
were not seated at table. The supper was arranged on the sideboard. Each had taken what he chose,

23:56.620 --> 24:01.120
and then stood about here and there in groups, their plates and glasses in their hands.

24:02.560 --> 24:08.600
Everyone seemed in high glee. Laughter and conversation were general and animated. Mr.

24:08.780 --> 24:13.540
Mason stood near the fire, talking to Colonel and Mrs. Dent, and appeared as merry as any

24:13.540 --> 24:14.100
of them.

24:14.660 --> 24:20.780
I filled a wine-glass. I saw Miss Ingram watch me frowningly as I did so. She thought I was

24:20.780 --> 24:27.020
taking a liberty, I dare say, and I returned to the library. Mr. Rochester's extreme pallor

24:27.020 --> 24:32.560
had disappeared, and he looked once more firm and stern. He took the glass from my hand.

24:33.460 --> 24:40.180
Here is to your health, minister and spirit, he said. He swallowed the contents and returned

24:40.180 --> 24:41.120
it to me.

24:41.680 --> 24:42.940
What are they doing, Jane?

24:43.900 --> 24:45.360
Laughing and talking, sir.

24:45.880 --> 24:50.580
They don't look grave and mysterious, as if they had heard something strange.

24:51.620 --> 24:54.660
Not at all. They are full of jests and gaiety.

24:55.300 --> 24:56.100
And Mason?

24:56.860 --> 24:58.440
He was laughing, too.

24:59.480 --> 25:03.520
If all these people came in a body and spat at me, what would you do, Jane?

25:04.800 --> 25:09.220
Turn them out of the room, sir, if I could. He half-smiled.

25:09.820 --> 25:15.600
But if I were to go to them, and they only looked at me coldly and whispered sneeringly

25:15.600 --> 25:20.460
amongst each other, and then dropped off and left me one by one, what then, would you go

25:20.460 --> 25:21.060
with them?

25:21.700 --> 25:26.040
I rather think not, sir. I should have more pleasure in staying with you.

25:26.480 --> 25:27.660
To comfort me?

25:28.880 --> 25:32.560
Yes, sir, to comfort you, as well as I could.

25:33.160 --> 25:36.480
And if they laid you under a ban for adhering to me?

25:36.480 --> 25:43.300
I probably should know nothing about their ban, and if I did, I should care nothing about it.

25:43.920 --> 25:46.200
Then you could dare censure for my sake.

25:46.860 --> 25:52.580
I could dare it for the sake of any friend who deserved my adherence, as you I am sure do.

25:53.900 --> 25:58.740
Go back now into the room, step quietly up to Mason, and whisper in his ear that Mr.

25:58.980 --> 26:03.740
Rochester has come and wishes to see him. Show him in here, and then leave me.

26:04.720 --> 26:05.840
Yes, sir.

26:06.780 --> 26:12.160
I did his behest. The company all stared at me as I passed straight among them. I sought

26:12.160 --> 26:17.960
Mr. Mason, delivered the message, and proceeded him from the room. I ushered him into the

26:17.960 --> 26:20.080
library, and then I went upstairs.

26:22.140 --> 26:27.240
At a late hour, after I had been in bed some time, I heard the visitors prepare to their

26:27.240 --> 26:31.460
chambers. I distinguished Mr. Rochester's voice, and heard him say,

26:31.460 --> 26:34.160
This way, Mason. This is your room.

26:35.420 --> 26:41.100
He spoke cheerfully. The gay tones set my heart at ease. I was soon asleep.

